sch:rule.sch:assert:
The first <title> element under a <titleStmt> element must have 
@level attribute with a value of "m" indicating "monographic" or "a" indicating
analytic.

constraint.sch:assert:
@ref attributes on
                    <persName> elements must contain a properly formatted Syriaca.org person
                    URI that starts with 'http://syriaca.org/person/'.

@ref attributes on
                    <placeName> elements must contain a properly formatted Syriaca.org place
                    URI that starts with 'http://syriaca.org/place/'.

sch:rule.sch:assert:
@mutual attributes on <relation> elements of relation factoids must
                      contain a properly formatted Syriaca.org person URI that starts with
                      'http://syriaca.org/person/'.

@active attributes on <relation> elements of relation factoids must
                      contain a properly formatted Syriaca.org person URI that starts with
                      'http://syriaca.org/person/'.

@passive attributes on <relation> elements of relation factoids must
                      contain a properly formatted Syriaca.org person URI that starts with
                      'http://syriaca.org/person/'.

remarks.p:
This customization removes from the <relation> element all attributes except
              @name, @type, @ana, @mutual, @passive, and @active. It also restricts values for the
              @name, @type, and @ana attributes and requires the encoder to use the @name and @ana
              attributes.
